Introduction

This is a digest of results from a battery of accessibility Tests.

The battery includes 1353 automated accessibility tests drawn from ten different packages: Alfa, Axe, Continuum, Equal Access, HTML CodeSniffer, Nu Html Checker, QualWeb, Tenon, Testaro, and WAVE.

These tests were run on the web page named above and gave the page a score of 1778, where 0 would be perfect.

Issue summary

Special issues

log: Score 132. This is based on the amount of browser error logging and miscellaneous logging during the tests.

solos: Score 70. This is based on issues reported by unclassified tests. Details are in the report.

Classified issues

Issue linkNoText

WCAG: 2.4.4

Score: 197

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r11, score 36 (Link has no accessible name)
  • Package axe, test link-name, score 27 (Link has no discernible text)
  • Package continuum, test 237, score 36 (a element has no mechanism that allows an accessible name value to be calculated)
  • Package htmlcs, test e:AAA.4_1_2.H91.A.NoContent, score 44 (Link has an href attribute but no text)
  • Package ibm, test WCAG20_A_HasText, score 40 (Hyperlink has no text description)
  • Package wave, test e:link_empty, score 44 (Link contains no text)
  • Package tenon, test 57, score 80 (Link has no text inside it)
  • Package tenon, test 91, score 24 (Link has a background image but no text inside it)

Issue textContrastAA

WCAG: 1.4.3

Score: 126

Issue reports in this category:

  • Package alfa, test r69, score 96 (Text outside widget has subminimum contrast)
  • Package axe, test color-contrast, score 34 (Element has insufficient color contrast)
  • Package htmlcs, test e:AAA.1_4_6.G18.Fail, score 4 (Contrast between the text and its background is less than 4.5:1)
  • Package qualWeb, test QW-ACT-R37, score 22 (Text has less than the minimum contrast)
  • Package wave, test c:contrast, score 9 (Very low contrast)
